<p class="">I refer the Parliamentary Secretary to various issues of "Motor Transport," a well-known trade paper, beginning any time after the first of this year, in which, on the first page, he will find a number of references to luncheons given by the Association of British Chambers of Commerce and to conversations of one sort and another between the then Minister and these bodies. These copies are in the Library now and can be found in a few moments.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
